title: Done deal: Dockers land Bennell
text:
AFL Trades 2015: Fremantle Dockers secure Harley Bennell in trade Chris Robinson PerthNow AFL Trades 2015: Fremantle Dockers secure Harley Bennell in trade Chris Robinson PerthNow Cats pick up Lachie Henderson 0:30 
AFL: Geelong continue to strengthen their squad, picking up Cats pick up Lachie Henderson from Carlton October 14th 2015 5 hours ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/AFL/News/ 
FREMANTLE has secured the services of troubled Gold Coast midfielder Harley Bennell after agreeing to a trade with the Suns. 
The Dockers signed Bennell to a three-year contract and also gained pick 22 in the upcoming draft. In return, Fremantle gave up its first-round pick (16) as well as pick 35. 
“I’m excited about returning home to WA and joining Fremantle,” Bennell said. 
“I want to thank the Gold Coast for drafting me and the support they have offered me during my time at the club. 
“My main focus now is to knuckle down and have a solid pre-season over the coming months.” 
An undisputed talent on the field, Bennell struggled with off-field issues in 2015, culminating in an alleged drunken altercation last month that led to the Suns committing to a trade. Other Stories
